All API endpoints return a consistent response envelope structure: 
```json
{ 
  "data": null, 
  "error": { "code": "string", "message": "string" }, 
  "meta": { "page": "number", "perPage": "number", "total": "number" } 
}
```
In this structure, `data` contains the payload (null on errors), `error` contains the error details (null on success), and `meta` provides pagination information.
